itemDescription: English botanist and missionary for the Quaker church in Australia (1794-1869)

wikipedia_page.main: See also [1] for two other James Backhouse botanists and nursery owners of York.James Backhouse (8 July 1794 – 20 January 1869) was a botanist and missionary for the Quaker church in Australia. His son, also James Backhouse (1825–1890), was also a botanist.
